                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1723.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Johnson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-26T15:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1915—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Nashville</hi> arrived 23d. Country quiet on the surface
                    except Macoris and La Romana. News just received that rebels took latter town
                    yesterday sacking it and destroying customhouse records and left going towards
                    Macoris. Government has despatched more troops but preferred <hi rend="italic"
                        >Nashville</hi> to remain here where Government sees possibilities of
                    trouble.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
